Privacy Policy
Phlow, Inc. has developed the Phlow app as a premium service. This document serves to educate our users about our practices concerning the gathering, utilization, and revelation of Personal Information for those who decide to use our Service.
By opting to use our Service, you consent to the collection and utilization of information in accordance with this policy. The Personal Information we gather is employed for enhancing and delivering the Service. We pledge not to use or share your information with anyone, except as outlined in this Privacy Policy.
This Privacy Policy's terminology is consistent with that in our Terms and Conditions, available at Phlow, unless specified otherwise within this Privacy Policy.
Information Collection and Use
To enrich your experience with our Service, we may require certain personally identifiable information. Rest assured, the information we collect will be kept by us and used in accordance with this privacy policy.
Our app utilizes third-party services which might gather information to recognize you.
General Data Collection and Retention:
At Phlow, Inc., safeguarding user privacy and securing data is of paramount importance. Generally, we abstain from collecting user data or storing it on our servers. User information, including personal and app usage data, is exclusively stored on the user's device, ensuring total user control over their data.
User Data Deletion
Users have the right to remove their data by uninstalling the Phlow app from their device. Upon deletion of the app, all data stored locally, encompassing personal information and app usage data, is irrevocably eliminated from the user's device. Post-deletion, we do not retain any user data.
Log Data
Please be aware that in the event of an app error, we collect data and information (via third-party products) on your phone termed as Log Data. This may include details like your device's Internet Protocol ("IP") address, device name, operating system version, app configuration during Service use, along with the date and time of your Service use, and other statistics.
Cookies
Cookies are small data files used as unique, anonymous identifiers. Sent from the websites you visit, they are stored on your device's internal memory.
Our Service does not explicitly employ "cookies". However, the app might use third-party code and libraries that utilize "cookies" to gather information and enhance their services. You can choose to accept or refuse these cookies and be notified when a cookie is being sent to your device. If you refuse our cookies, some parts of this Service may not be accessible to you.
Service Providers
We engage third-party companies and individuals for reasons such as:
Facilitating our Service;
Providing the Service on our behalf;
Performing Service-related services; or
Helping us understand how our Service is utilized.
We inform our Service users that these third parties may have access to your Personal Information. Their role is to perform tasks on our behalf, but they are obligated not to disclose or use the information for other purposes.
Security
Your trust in providing us your Personal Information is highly valued, and we strive to protect it with commercially viable means. However, no internet transmission or electronic storage method is 100% secure, so we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
Links to Other Sites
Our Service may include links to external sites. Clicking on a third-party link will direct you to that site. These sites are not operated by us, and we strongly recommend reviewing their Privacy Policies. We do not control and are not responsible for the content, privacy policies, or practices of any third-party sites or services.
Children's Privacy
Our Services are not intended for individuals under the age of 13. We do not intentionally collect personally identifiable information from children under 13. If we learn that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, we will promptly delete it from our servers. If you are a parent or guardian aware that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us to take necessary measures.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may periodically update our Privacy Policy. You are encouraged to review this page regularly for any changes. Changes to the Privacy Policy will be communicated by posting the updated policy on this page.
